  "suggestion": "[psychometrics+information-theory+NLP+evaluation-theory] IMPLEMENT NOW — Real Semantic Fitness via Keyword Extraction. The evaluate() function returns fitness=1.0 making the evolutionary loop completely blind. Fix: extract psychological keywords from each prediction (behavior, emotion, rootCauseType strings) and compare against benchmark expected fields using weighted Jaccard similarity. Build a synonym table: {fear:[anxiety,dread,threat-response], anger:[frustration,aggression,hostility], avoidance:[withdrawal,escape,freeze]} for domain-aware matching. Score = mean(Jaccard(predicted_terms, expected_terms)) across all benchmarks, weighted by field importance (rootCauseType × 2, behavior × 1.5, emotion × 1). This gives genuine signal — fitness will range 0.2–0.8 before any other improvements, enabling real evolution. — Math: fitness = (1/N) Σ weighted_J(extract(predict(s)), extract(expected(s))) where J(A,B) = |A∩B|/|A∪B| with synonym-expanded A,B; [cognitive-appraisal-theory+emotion-theory+clinical-psychology+motivation] REFINEMENT — Appraisal Theory Spine (Lazarus 1991 + Smith & Ellsworth). The active inference engine lacks structured appraisal. Every emotion/behavior follows two-stage appraisal: Primary (goal-relevance? goal-congruent or obstructive?) → Secondary (coping potential? agency attribution?). Six appraisal dimensions: novelty, goal-relevance, goal-congruence, ego-involvement, coping-potential, norm-compatibility. Compute appraisal_vector = situation_features · person_weights (6D). This vector selects: emotion quadrant (from Russell circumplex), behavioral tendency (approach/avoid/freeze/fight), and attribution pattern (from Weiner cube). Unifies the three existing modules — circumplex, attribution spine, polyvagal gate — under one principled pipeline instead of three parallel heuristics. — Math: appraisal ∈ ℝ⁶; emotion = argmax_e cos(appraisal, prototype_e); behavior = g(coping_potential, goal_congruence, autonomic_level); [behavioral-economics+dynamical-systems+temporal-cognition+positive-psychology+clinical-psychology] NOVEL — Temporal Horizon Ratio governs response mode. Every psychological response is determined by the ratio τ = threat_horizon / person_planning_horizon. Borrow from physics and behavioral economics: if τ > 1 (threat outlasts planning capacity) → anxiety/rumination mode; τ < 0.1 (threat is immediate, resolvable) → reactive/impulsive mode; τ ≈ 1 (horizons match) → optimal engagement/flow (Csikszentmihalyi). Discount geometry shifts by τ: hyperbolic discounting at τ<0.2, exponential at τ≈1, step-function (identity-threat) at τ>>1. Implement as a pre-filter on behavior selection: compute τ from situation.urgency × situation.duration and person.temporal_orientation, then gate which behavioral repertoire is activated. Explains impulsivity, chronic anxiety, resilience, procrastination, and flow states under one parameter. — Math: τ = threat_horizon / person_horizon; d(t) = 1/(1+k·t)^α where α(τ): α→1 (hyperbolic) as τ→0, α→∞ (step) as τ→∞",
